<% content_for(:title, "Privacy Policy") %>

<div class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto">
  <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl text-walnut tracking-wide mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-walnut/70 mb-8">Last updated: 11 March 2026</p>

  <div class="space-y-8 text-walnut/80 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
    <section>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl text-walnut mb-3">Data controller</h2>
      <p>
        Course Imports is operated as an independent project. For data protection queries, contact
        <a href="mailto:privacy@courseimports.com" class="text-rose hover:text-rose-dark underline">privacy@courseimports.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl text-walnut mb-3">What data we collect</h2>
      <p>When you sign in with GitHub, we receive and store the following from your GitHub profile:</p>
      <ul class="mt-2 ml-5 list-disc space-y-1">
        <li>GitHub username</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Avatar URL</li>
        <li>GitHub user ID</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-3">
        When you submit a course, we store the repository URL and metadata fetched from GitHub
        (title, description, topics, author name).
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl text-walnut mb-3">Why we process your data</h2>
      <p>We process your data for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul class="mt-2 ml-5 list-disc space-y-1">
        <li>To authenticate you and manage your account</li>
        <li>To display your submitted courses in the public registry</li>
        <li>To validate course repositories via the GitHub API</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl text-walnut mb-3">Legal basis</h2>
      <p>Under UK GDPR Article 6, we process your data on the following bases:</p>
      <ul class="mt-2 ml-5 list-disc space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> (Article 6(1)(f)) — operating the registry and displaying submitted courses</li>
        <li><strong>Consent</strong> (Article 6(1)(a)) — you choose to sign in with GitHub and submit courses</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl text-walnut mb-3">Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        Your account data is retained for as long as your account exists. If you delete your account,
        all associated personal data is removed. Course metadata may be retained in anonymised form.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl text-walnut mb-3">Third-party sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not sell or share your personal data with third parties. The following services process data on our behalf:</p>
      <ul class="mt-2 ml-5 list-disc space-y-1">
        <li><strong>GitHub</strong> — authentication provider; subject to <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" class="text-rose hover:text-rose-dark underline">GitHub's privacy statement</a></li>
        <li><strong>Hosting provider</strong> — servers are located in the EU; your data may be transmitted to and stored on these servers</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl text-walnut mb-3">Cookies</h2>
      <p>This site uses two cookies, both strictly necessary:</p>
      <ul class="mt-2 ml-5 list-disc space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Session cookie</strong> (<code class="text-sm bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">_course_imports_api_session</code>) — keeps you signed in; expires when you close your browser</li>
        <li><strong>Cookie notice</strong> (<code class="text-sm bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">cookie_consent</code>) — records that you have seen the cookie notice; expires after 365 days</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-3">We do not use analytics, tracking, or advertising cookies.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl text-walnut mb-3">Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul class="mt-2 ml-5 list-disc space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — ask us to correct inaccurate data</li>
        <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — ask us to delete your data and account</li>
        <li><strong>Portability</strong> — receive your data in a machine-readable format</li>
        <li><strong>Object</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
        <li><strong>Complaint</strong> — lodge a complaint with the <a href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/" class="text-rose hover:text-rose-dark underline">Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-3">
        To exercise any of these rights, contact
        <a href="mailto:privacy@courseimports.com" class="text-rose hover:text-rose-dark underline">privacy@courseimports.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl text-walnut mb-3">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. The "last updated" date at the top of this page
        will be revised accordingly.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
